CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=cfut_your_api_token_here
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=your_account_id_here
# Local-only token file (never committed).
# Copy values from here to your .env for local reference.
#
# For Git push auto-deploy (the ONLY deployment method):
#   1. Put the real values in your LOCAL .env (gitignored).
#   2. In Cloudflare Dashboard → your Worker → Settings → Builds:
#      Add them as SECRETS under "Build variables and secrets":
#        - CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN (required for all builds)
#        - CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID (optional)
# This way ALL Git-triggered builds use exactly the token from your .env.
